{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.80",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 80,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 80 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:1",
      "text": "Give ear, O Shepherd of Israel, thou who leadest Joseph like a flock! Thou who art enthroned upon the cherubim, shine forth",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:2",
      "text": "before Ephraim and Benjamin and Manasseh! Stir up thy might, and come to save us!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:3",
      "text": "Restore us, O God; let thy face shine, that we may be saved!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:4",
      "text": "O Lord God of hosts, how long wilt thou be angry with thy people's prayers?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:5",
      "text": "Thou hast fed them with the bread of tears, and given them tears to drink in full measure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:6",
      "text": "Thou dost make us the scorn of our neighbors; and our enemies laugh among themselves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:7",
      "text": "Restore us, O God of hosts; let thy face shine, that we may be saved!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:8",
      "text": "Thou didst bring a vine out of Egypt; thou didst drive out the nations and plant it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:9",
      "text": "Thou didst clear the ground for it; it took deep root and filled the land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:10",
      "text": "The mountains were covered with its shade, the mighty cedars with its branches;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:11",
      "text": "it sent out its branches to the sea, and its shoots to the River.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:12",
      "text": "Why then hast thou broken down its walls, so that all who pass along the way pluck its fruit?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:13",
      "text": "The boar from the forest ravages it, and all that move in the field feed on it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:14",
      "text": "Turn again, O God of hosts! Look down from heaven, and see; have regard for this vine,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:15",
      "text": "the stock which thy right hand planted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:16",
      "text": "They have burned it with fire, they have cut it down; may they perish at the rebuke of thy countenance!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:17",
      "text": "But let thy hand be upon the man of thy right hand, the son of man whom thou hast made strong for thyself!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:18",
      "text": "Then we will never turn back from thee; give us life, and we will call on thy name!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.80.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 80,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 80:19",
      "text": "Restore us, O Lord God of hosts! let thy face shine, that we may be saved!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
